+Continue in the current accepted PlaySyncer workspace.
+
+PS-03D1-1 is approved and closed.
+
+Start only:
+
+PS-03D1-2A — Account Domain Service Implementation
+
+قبل از پاسخ دادن عجله نکن. اول مسئله، سورس، فایل‌ها، وابستگی‌ها، ریسک‌ها و اثرات جانبی را عمیق تحلیل کن. اگر شواهد کافی از سورس، لاگ، diff یا تست نداری، ادعای قطعی نکن. خروجی سطحی، حدسی، تبلیغاتی یا سریع نده. هر پیشنهاد کدنویسی باید کوچک، قابل تست، قابل rollback و سازگار با استانداردهای فعلی پروژه باشد. اگر چیزی خارج از scope است فقط گزارش بده و بدون تأیید من patch یا refactor پیشنهاد نکن. قبل از ارائه راه‌حل، تفاوت Fact، Assumption، Risk و Recommendation را مشخص کن.
+
+This stage authorizes implementation of the Account Domain Service and its tests only.
+
+Do not:
+
+- activate any Account API route
+- update OpenAPI
+- regenerate API clients
+- connect the frontend
+- implement Secret Reveal
+- implement Customer Assignment
+- change the database schema
+- create or modify migrations
+- run drizzle-kit push
+- write to the live database
+- add dependencies
+- create or expose a real production secret
+- perform unrelated refactoring
+
+Implement the smallest safe Account Domain Service based on the approved PS-03D1-1 design.
+
+Required behavior:
+
+1. Create a focused Account service under:
+
+artifacts/api-server/src/services/account/
+
+Keep the structure simple. Do not split the service into unnecessary files.
+
+2. Implement a key loader for:
+
+PLAYSYNCER_ACCOUNT_MASTER_KEY
+
+Rules:
+
+- value must be valid Base64
+- decoded value must be exactly 32 bytes
+- use Node.js built-in crypto/HKDF
+- derive separate encryption and lookup-hash subkeys
+- missing or invalid key must stop Account creation
+- never log the key or plaintext credentials
+- tests must use a synthetic test key
+- do not create the real Replit Secret in this stage
+
+3. Implement Account creation input validation:
+
+- valid gameId UUID
+- required PSN Email
+- required PSN Password
+- required Email Password
+- required Online ID
+- required birthDate in YYYY-MM-DD format
+- required Family Management Email
+- required backupCodes with at least one non-empty code
+- optional internal confirmed boolean
+- statusOverride must not be accepted
+
+4. Normalize values:
+
+- PSN Email: trim and lowercase
+- Family Management Email: trim and lowercase
+- Online ID: trim and store with its entered letter case
+- duplicate comparison for Online ID: case-insensitive
+- Backup Codes: trim and reject empty values
+
+5. Before creating an Account:
+
+- require an existing non-deleted Game
+- reject Account creation when the Game is INACTIVE
+- detect duplicates for:
+  - PSN Email
+  - Online ID
+  - Family Management Email
+
+When duplicates exist and confirmed is false:
+
+- return a typed duplicate-warning result
+- include only duplicate field names
+- write nothing to the database
+
+When confirmed is true:
+
+- allow creation to continue
+
+6. Account identifiers:
+
+- global format: ACC-000001
+- per-game format: GTA6-001
+- no leading # character
+- use account_code_seq for the global number
+- never use MAX + 1
+- create the per-game sequence row with ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING
+- allocate the per-game number with UPDATE ... RETURNING
+- created or deleted Account identifiers must never be reused
+- a failed transaction may reuse its rolled-back per-game number
+- gaps in the global sequence are acceptable
+
+7. Encrypt and store:
+
+- PSN Email
+- PSN Password
+- Email Password
+- Family Management Email
+- each Backup Code separately
+
+Create lookup hashes for the approved Account fields.
+
+Do not create a lookup hash for Backup Codes.
+
+8. Create Capacity rows automatically from the Game platform using the existing capacity-definition helper.
+
+Keep:
+
+Z3_SHARED_PS5_PS4
+instanceNo = 0
+
+Do not manually create or remove Capacity definitions.
+
+9. Perform all Account creation writes in one database transaction:
+
+- identifier allocation
+- Account insert
+- Capacity inserts
+- Backup Code inserts
+
+If any step fails, no partial Account, Capacity or Backup Code rows may remain.
+
+10. A newly created Account must have:
+
+statusOverride = null
+
+Do not persist AVAILABLE, PARTIALLY_SOLD or automatic SOLD as an Account status column.
+
+11. Return only a safe Domain result containing non-secret Account information.
+
+Do not return:
+
+- plaintext credentials
+- ciphertext
+- lookup hashes
+- Backup Codes
+- encryption keys
+
+12. Add focused tests covering at minimum:
+
+- valid creation
+- all three Game platforms and their Capacity rows
+- global and per-game identifier formatting
+- no leading # in display number
+- required Backup Code
+- invalid birth date
+- inactive Game rejection
+- missing or invalid master key
+- successful encryption and non-plaintext storage
+- duplicate warning with no database write
+- confirmed duplicate creation
+- safe result without secrets
+- rollback when Account creation fails
+- rollback when Backup Code insertion fails
+- two concurrent creations for the same Game receive different identifiers
+
+Use only disposable test databases or the existing isolated test harness.
+
+Do not write Account test data to the live workspace database.
+
+13. Keep the Account routes disabled.
+
+The existing disabled-route safety tests must continue to pass.
+
+14. Run and report actual exit codes for:
+
+- pnpm run typecheck
+- pnpm --filter @workspace/api-server run test
+- pnpm --filter @workspace/db run test
+- pnpm --filter @workspace/db run test:migrations
+- PORT=24351 BASE_PATH=/ pnpm --filter @workspace/playsyncer run build
+
+15. Update only the relevant phase documentation to show that PS-03D1-2A implementation is awaiting review.
+
+Do not commit the changes yet.
+
+Return:
+
+- exact files created and modified
+- a simple summary of what was implemented
+- tests added
+- actual test counts and exit codes
+- confirmation that no route, migration, schema, OpenAPI or live database change occurred
+- remaining risks or blockers
+- git diff summary
+- git status
+
+Final status must be exactly one of:
+
+- PS-03D1-2A — IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE, AWAITING COMMAND CENTER REVIEW
+- PS-03D1-2A — INCOMPLETE
+- PS-03D1-2A — TEST FAILURE
+- PS-03D1-2A — SCOPE OR DATABASE SAFETY VIOLATION
\ No newline at end of file
